<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-03-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="63" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d63">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/262.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Lee</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-03-29"><hi rend="italic">March 29,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reports that Tegucigalpa was abandoned early yesterday and occupied last
                            night by forces of Nicaragua and revolutionists. Also reports that
                            Chargé Brown advises assumed charge with consuls to preserve order.
                            Further reports that official announcement has been received here that
                            forces of Nicaragua were bombarding Amapala to-day at noon and that
                            general complication is to be feared.</p>
                    </div>
